The Proposal: -

Statements are made to the government from time to time by their families regarding various problems faced by the police in the state. Coordination Committee to discuss and resolve the issues / difficulties faced by the families of police personnel.
The issue of consolidation was under the consideration of the government. In this regard, the Government has decided to: -
The Government's Decisions:
The following Coordination Committee is being constituted to address various issues / grievances of Police families in the State: -

para_trans: Government Decision No: Pokua-1216 / P.No.855 / Pol-7
The coordination committee deals with the problems faced by the families of police personnel, such as skills.
Providing employment opportunities through the program, housing, health, etc.
It will suggest measures to the government to address it through consultation.
This Government decision is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
